  "title": "Core Concepts of Foundations of Object-Oriented Programming in Java",
  "lessonText": "This lesson introduces the fundamental principles of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Java.",
  "data": {
    "content": "Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) is a programming paradigm based on the concept of objects.\n\n- **Encapsulation**: Bundles data and methods that operate on the data within a single unit (class).\n- **Abstraction**: Hides complex implementation details and exposes only the necessary features of an object.\n- **Inheritance**: Allows a new class to inherit properties and methods from an existing class, promoting code reusability.\n- **Polymorphism**: Enables objects to be treated as instances of their parent class, allowing for method overriding and overloading.\n\nUnderstanding these core concepts is crucial for effective Java programming and for working with data structures."
  }
}
